    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into chips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-chicken-breast-with-slaw-sweet-potato-chips-and-gravy/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-chicken-breast-with-slaw-sweet-potato-chips-and-gravy/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>chicken </strong>in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces</p><p>Add your <strong>southern fried seasoning </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a large bowl with 4 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[6 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [8 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>halved chicken</strong> to the bowl with 2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up so the chicken is evenly coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-chicken-breast-with-slaw-sweet-potato-chips-and-gravy/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to coat the bottom of the pan) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, reduce the heat to medium-high and add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>to the pan and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden, crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p><p>Once done, season the <strong>cooked chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>southern fried chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-chicken-breast-with-slaw-sweet-potato-chips-and-gravy/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-chicken-breast-with-slaw-sweet-potato-chips-and-gravy/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-chicken-breast-with-slaw-sweet-potato-chips-and-gravy/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>gravy base</strong> with 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and whisk thoroughly</p><p>Pour the <strong>gravy mix</strong> into the pan with the garlic and cook for 2-3 min, stirring regularly, or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/southern-fried-chicken-breast-with-slaw-sweet-potato-chips-and-gravy/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>southern fried chicken</strong> with the <strong>creamy slaw</strong>, <strong>chips</strong> and <strong>gravy</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
